Open Source for Public Good

Building Digital Public Infrastructure

Empowering governments and communities through innovative open-source software solutions, fostering transparency, efficiency, and inclusive digital transformation globally. We've been passionately developing large-scale open-source solutions for over 15 years, collaborating with governments and communities to tackle pressing challenges from disaster management and elections to education and environmental sustainability.

FAQ

Have any question? Find answer here.

What is Lanka Software Foundation ?

Lanka Software Foundation (LSF) is Non-governmental non profit organization to support technical upgradation of Sri Lanka's public infrastructure and beyond to the global governments by helping digital solution designing, and open-source community's works.

How can I get involved with LSF projects and help them?

Starting from our "Get Involved" page would be ideal. Here you can choose the current project you are most interested in and can handle from a list. We welcome hobbyists as well as developers, scholars, legislators, and more.

What kinds of projects do LSF funds?

LSF encourages the incubation of open-source projects which are innovative in nature and predominantly serve digital governance, public infrastructure, e-government, digital identity, finance, etc.

Are there mentorship or internship opportunities available at LSF?

LSF offers mentorship and internship programs that provide professional guidance and hands-on exposure along with certain other advantages such as networking and career development in technology and open-source domains.

Who are LSF‚Äôs main partners and collaborators?

LSF has a worldwide view of the collaborations like governments, international institutions, universities, private-sector technology entrepreneurs, and open-source communities working together on cutting-edge digital transformation projects.
